The paper discusses a new algorithm for finding neighborhoods among data points using geometric patterns, which is relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of Apollonius circle, which is a well-known concept in computational geometry and can be categorized under cs.CG. The algorithm's aim is to identify the neighborhood state of data points, which is a common problem in machine learning and can be categorized under cs.LG. The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed algorithm, which can be categorized under cs.SI (systems and control) and cs.IT (information theory).
